# Environment variables — DENSO sense website
#
# FRONTEND (Vite static build): requires NO environment variables.
# `npm run dev` and `npm run build` work with nothing set.
#
# BACKEND (Azure Static Web Apps managed Function under /api):
# the "Request a Demo" form (POST /api/demo-request) stores leads in an
# Azure Table. These are configured as Azure SWA *Application settings*
# (Portal → Static Web App → Settings → Configuration), NOT committed here.
# For LOCAL function dev, put them in api/local.settings.json (git-ignored).
#
# Required:
# STORAGE_CONNECTION_STRING=    # connection string of the Azure Storage account that holds the leads table
#                               # (Storage account → Access keys → Connection string)
# Optional:
# DEMO_TABLE_NAME=demosubmissions   # table name to write leads into (defaults to "demosubmissions")
